.TH ISOCMD 1 "April 2026" "Iso Commander 6.3.5" "Iso-Commander Manual"

.SH NAME
Iso Commander (isocmd) \- Command-line utility for managing .iso files and converting image formats.

.SH DESCRIPTION
Iso Commander (isocmd) is a command-line utility for managing .iso files and converting various image formats to .iso using asynchronous I/O operations and multi-threaded processing.

.SH NON-INTERACTIVE COMMANDS
.TP
.B -v, --version
.br
Show program version.

.TP
.B --silent
.br
Suppress informational, error and warning output.

.TP
.B -d\<N\>
.br
Set max directory recursion depth when scanning for ISOs; default is -1 (unlimited).

.TP
.B mount
.br
Mount one or more ISO files or directories containing ISOs. Requires root.

.TP
.B umount, unmount
.br
Unmount ISO mount points. Without arguments or with "all", unmounts all under /mnt. Requires root.

.SH EXAMPLES

.TP
Mount specific ISOs:
.br
\fBisocmd /path/to/file1.iso /path/to/file2.iso mount\fR

.TP
Mount all ISOs within a directory:
.br
\fBisocmd /path/to/dir mount\fR

.TP
Mount all ISOs within a directory up to depth 2:
.br
\fBisocmd -d2 /path/to/dir mount\fR

.TP
Mount an ISO silently:
.br
\fBisocmd --silent /path/to/file.iso mount\fR

.TP
Unmount ISO mount points:
.br
\fBisocmd /mnt/iso_example /mnt/iso_other umount\fR

.TP
Unmount all ISO mount points:
.br
\fBisocmd all umount or isocmd umount\fR

.SH UI INTERACTIVE OPTIONS AND FEATURES
.TP
.B ManageISO
Mount, Umount, Delete, Move, Copy, and Write ISO files. Note that Write retains bootable status for USB drives.

.TP
.B Convert2ISO
Converts .bin, .img, .mdf, and .nrg files to .iso. Ported from original C tools (mdf2iso, nrg2iso, ccd2iso).

.TP
.B ImportISO
Creates/updates an ISO database (~10,000 entries max) at \fI~/.local/share/isocmd/database/iso_commander_database.txt\fR.

.SH CONFIGURATION
The configuration file is located at \fI~/.config/isocmd/config\fR.

.SS GENERAL SETTINGS
.TP
.B auto_update
Enable background metadata updates from folder history. (on/off)
.TP
.B filenames_only
Display only filenames instead of full paths. Acts as a global override for all list display modes except for the unmount list. (on/off)
.TP
.B pagination
Items per page in list view. (0 to disable)

.SS HISTORY SETTINGS
.TP
.B folder_path_history_lines
Max unique folder paths to persist in history. (Default: 100)
.TP
.B filter_history_lines
Max unique search filters to persist in history. (Default: 50)

.SS DISPLAY MODES
Controls whether lists are shown in \fBfull\fR or \fBcompact\fR format. Options include:
.B mount_list, umount_list, cp_mv_rm_list, write_list, conversion_lists.

.SS THREAD CONFIGURATION
Iso Commander uses a multi-threaded architecture to speed up I/O and UI operations.
.TP
.B max_thread_cap
Global maximum concurrent threads allowed. (Default: 32)
.TP
.B threads_for_cp_mv
Threads allocated for copy/move tasks.
.TP
.B threads_for_conversions
Threads allocated for ISO file conversions.
.TP
.B threads_for_mount / threads_for_umount
Threads allocated for mounting and unmounting tasks.
.TP
.B threads_for_database_cleanup
Threads allocated for database maintenance.
.TP
.B threads_for_rm
Threads allocated for file removal tasks.
.TP
.B threads_for_list_sorting / threads_for_list_filtering
Threads allocated for UI responsiveness and list processing.

